properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 14 at 2:46PM CST until February 15 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...BLOWING SNOW LEADING TO ICY ROADS FROM WEST CENTRAL INTO SOUTH
CENTRAL MINNESOTA INTO TONIGHT...

.Strong south winds have resulted in blowing snow from west
central to south central Minnesota in open areas outside of
cities. Though visibilities are not being significantly reduced,
as the snow blows over the roads, it is causing ice to form,
leading to slippery road conditions. Given the southerly wind
direction, the worst conditions are occurring on east to west
oriented roads.

* WHAT...Blowing snow. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of south central, southwest and west central
Minnesota.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Blowing snow will reduce visibility and lead to patchy
ice forming on roads. The hazardous conditions could impact the
evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT
